-- Carige says sells insurance units to Apollo for 310 mln euros
-- 
-- Tue Oct 28, 2014 04:25AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, Oct 28 (Reuters) - Italian bank Carige <CRGI.MI>, which must plug a capital shortfall of 810 million euros uncovered by Europe-wide stress tests of lenders, said on Tuesday it had reached a deal with Apollo Management Holdings to sell it its two insurance units.

Carige said in a statement sale proceeds would total 310 million euros which will be paid in cash upon closing of the deal, which is expected in the first quarter of next year.